<br>
When I first made my rogue I had absolutely no clue about this game, I didn’t even intend on playing the game for more than a couple of weeks.  So now here I am KOS in Neriak, worshiper of Bristlebane and level 46 wanting her epic BAD (yes I know that I can't do most things til 50).  What can I do to get into Neriak without getting plastered to the zone wall.  Mask o’ Deception doesn’t work…they sense my religion (the cheaters!!).  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalynntaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalynn Taranis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 3:22:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> You can't sneak/hide past them? I didn't think anything in Neriak could see through Sneak/hide.  You shouldn't be KoS to your guild with the DE mask on - at least I don't think you can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvaslin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaslin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Rogue Scholar</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 3:29:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> Bristlebane rogues should actually be amiable to the rogues in Neriak.<br>
<br>
Go figure. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwillaani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Willaani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 3:30:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> You ruined your faction elsewhere because any Rogue using the DE mask and following Bristlebane is Dubious in Neriak (which gets you everywhere in the city without Hide/Sneak).<br>
<br>
And to do the Epic, you don't even need the DE mask, just Hide/Sneak into the Rogue guild and stay behind Tani while PP'ing with Sneak up.  You stay Indiff as long as you remain Sneaking and behind the mob. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unneenairulan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nneena Irulan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 3:32:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> I don't believe I can sneak/hide in.  I **tried**the evil guild in freeport.  Yes...I got smacked down, almost before I hit the bottom of the stairs.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind I was in CB alot in my younger days.  I think they have a faction connection  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unneenairulan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nneena Irulan</A> at: 11/26/01 3:33:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udasnotkrekt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dasnot Krekt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 7:16:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> Howdy, very easy yet a bit of time to fix. Buy backpacks full of red wine and do wine quest in library in Neriak 3rd gate. My ROG worships Rodcet Nife, was kos to start withg in Neriak even with DE mask, after prolly close to 1k wines, went to ally as 1/2 elf. I did same thing as u, CB as a youngster, so only ones i have to worry bout r the WAR guild. Not hard to get round em at all. That should solve most of ur prolm i hope. =)<br>
<br>
<br>
Dasnot Krekt <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unpc01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NPC01</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 9:33:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> *** Bottle of Red Wine ...<br>
Related Creatures:<br>
(Nek3rd) Lokar ToBiath (Dark Bargainers)<br>
4 sets of 4 Bottle of Red Wine<br>
<br>
Factions Raised:<br>
Dark Bargainers<br>
Dread Guards Inner<br>
Dread Guards Outer<br>
<br>
Factions Lowered:<br>
None<br>
<br>
***<br>
<br>
This means you'll still have to watch walking past any of the guilds ... but heh ... its not like they're meant to like you,<br>
but the bulk of Nek is ok (esp banking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) ... I'm non-kos to guards even in High Elf form <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-<br>
Arcanum Veritas<br>
Beguiler of Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unikedemus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nikedemus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 1:30:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> Killing in CB only lowers faction with Indigo Brotherhood, which is the neriak warriors guild. Fortunatly, there are very few NPC's outside of the warrior guild on this faction. <br>
<br>
If you killed some other things that lowered your faction with the rogues guild, probably the best thing for you to do would be to make a dark elf necro and train Tanni to the zoneline, then log your rogue on and pick him there.<br>
<br>
-Nikedemus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urolemeggido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Role Meggido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 7:16:59 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> It is totally wrong that there is not a way to change your religion in eq.  <br>
<br>
A simple 6 - 12 hr quest is all that would be needed.  <br>
<br>
Give people who had no idea what religion meant (when it was far less important than it is today) years ago a way out.<br>
<br>
Better yet give people a /changereligion &lt;blah&gt; command that you can only activate once every 6 months. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 9:50:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> You can sneak/hide into Neriak.  My Indigo Brotherhood faction cannot possibly get any worse, and the Ebon Hand loves me.  I go banking in Neriak whenever I'm in the area.  Good place to buy poison components for the 70-90ish range as I recall (anti-summoned - good stuff for the Hole).<br>
<br>
The Dead (SKs and necros) don't like me much either, and there's an SK pat in the 2nd gate, so you'll basically have to keep sneaking until you get to the 3rd gate at a minimum.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalnac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valnac</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 10:18:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Epic Question: Religion!</span><hr size=1> /changereligion is good, but from a rpg perspective, I'd prefer to see the clerics get a skill or a spell &quot;convert,&quot; and the target could only be converted once ever.  Maybe it could be coded like the alignment change option on the FV server.<br>
<br>
